		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4109990)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4109990">
																		Necropost
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zerox1892" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2797341); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2797341&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250346" alt="Zerox1892" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2797341)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zerox1892" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2797341); return false;" >Zerox1892</a></span> <span class="odate time_1546744146 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Jan 2019 03:09</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4109990">
									

<p>What part of &quot;terms you're comfortable with&quot; did you not get?</p>
<p>The gist of his advice is to solve your problems with conflict and violence, regardless of how justifiable it might be to the reader given the protagonists situation.<br />
He could very well be telling her to eviscerate her boyfriend a.nd leave his corpse upon the pavement as a warning to her neighbors, but who would be comfortable following that advice?</p>
<p>He indicates that he is not going to destroy the world but is instead going to &quot;watch smart young people like you learn how to become the gods they've always dreamed of being&quot;. But hes not really watching her now is he?<br />
He's guiding her.<br />
To violence.<br />
And what is concerning is his claim of being the creepy uncle of the whole Universe. Who is to say he isn't giving the same advice to her boyfriend?</p>
<p>More importantly, what is a creepy uncle? Is it the uncle that tries to look up your skirt at a family reunion like in Madea’s Family Reunion? His advice/requests for her seem like sound advice on how to make real positive changes, which is perhaps nobler then asking for someone to bend over the grab them a soda to keep the simile going, but hes not a good uncle, hes a creepy one who has some sort of alternate motive. Much like in Family Reunion, and given his admission of being interested in watching the world not devouring it, I'd wager he's looking to watch her, and the universe at large, get violent for his amusement.</p>

							</div>

								
