														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2525658">
									

<p>I spent half of this article thinking this was a Jeff the Killer crossover for some reason&#8230; just by the name and the first few sentences.</p>
<p>Even though I started piecing together who this was about once 7 chains were mentioned, I still don't think it works. It's a cute little thought to entertain (this giant world-eater being some girl's self-help counselor), but I don't think it works. 2317 (if I got the # right) works because nobody knows what will happen when the seventh chain breaks, although it's strongly implied that it's going to be bad. This story just sucks the gravity out of the situation, even though it's not supposed to be taken that seriously.</p>
<p>I think this might've worked with a lot of dangerous SCPs, but 2317 isn't one of them.</p>

							</div>

								
					
